gal for code to move into the locked region. However,<br />it's not necessarily a *good* idea for code to move into the locked<br />region, so the two barriers are likely the RightThing(tm). But the two<br />barriers are what makes me think that the C version really isn't any<br />better. And the OOSTORE case then just clinches the deal for me.<br /><br />                         Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
